Phase 5: Implement GCI0020 Resource Exhaustion Pattern Detection

Detects common patterns leading to resource exhaustion vulnerabilities:

Pattern 1: Timeout/Deadline Removal (80% confidence)
  - Flags removed timeout/TimeSpan assignments
  - Prevents indefinite operations

Pattern 2: Iteration Limit Removal (80% confidence)
  - Detects removed loop limits (maxIterations, etc.)
  - Catches infinite loop vulnerabilities like CVE-2019-0981

Pattern 3: Resource Allocation Increase (70% confidence)
  - Flags significant increases in connection/thread limits
  - 5x threshold to avoid over-flagging

Pattern 4: Resource Cleanup Removal (75% confidence)
  - Detects using statement / Dispose call removal
  - Prevents resource leaks

Pattern 5: Async Operation Addition (65% confidence)
  - Flags new Task.Run/Task.Factory usage
  - Warns about unbounded concurrency

